<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">which itself</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 comes from the Celtic Renos, literally "that which flows", from the Proto-Indo-European root *rei- ("to flow, run"), which is also the origin of the English verb "to run" and the Greek adage Πάντα ῥεῖ καὶ οὐδὲν μένει, (everything flows, nothing stands still).
